description: The Himachal Pradesh High Court deemed the appointment of six Congress MLAs as chief parliamentary secretaries unconstitutional.  The court declared the appointments void and ordered the immediate withdrawal of all privileges and facilities, stating the appointments were outside the legislative authority of the state assembly.
title: High court voids Himachal’s appointment of 6 parliamentary secretaries
6 with 10,000 charas chocolates held in Karnataka

description: In Uttar Pradesh, authorities demolished multiple homes following a gunfight, dacoity, and Muharram clashes, leaving families homeless and struggling.  Victims recount the trauma of losing their homes and possessions, with some forced to leave their town and children's educations disrupted. They question the justice of being punished for the alleged crimes of family members.
title: SC slams bulldozer brakes, but it comes too late for many

description: An Ahmedabad policeman, Virendrasinh Padheria, has been arrested in Punjab for the murder of MICA student Priyanshu Jain. Padheria, who was on leave, allegedly stabbed Jain after a road rage incident on November 10th. Police used advanced tracking and human intelligence to locate and apprehend the accused.
title: Gujarat cop held in Punjab for killing MICA student after road rage

description: Gwalior DSP Santosh Patel had a heartwarming reunion with Salman Khan, a Bhopal vegetable vendor who helped him during his struggling days as a student.  Patel, who often ran out of money, received free vegetables from Khan. Years later, Patel, now a DSP, met Khan and thanked him for his kindness, sharing their story on social media.
title: Kindness repays a visit 14 years on as cop meets supportive vendor

description: The Chhattisgarh High Court dismissed three FIRs against IPS officer G P Singh. The court found the FIRs, which included charges of sedition, extortion, and disproportionate assets, to be baseless. The court determined that the FIRs lacked evidence and appeared to be intended for harassment. Singh, an ADGP at the time of the FIRs, was cleared of all charges.
title: HC cites lack of proof, junks sedition, extortion FIRs against IPS officer

description: The Calcutta High Court, while refusing to impose a gag order on a former BJP leader, emphasized that freedom of expression doesn't permit abuse or incite violence. The court, hearing the leader's anticipatory bail plea, acknowledged her right to free speech but expressed disapproval of her social media post, terming it as containing "unwarranted insinuations" against a religious community.
title: Freedom of expression is not licence to abuse, says HC, but shuns gag order

description: The Supreme Court of India has laid down a strict procedure for authorities to follow before demolishing illegal structures.  A 15-day notice period, a personal hearing, and a final order with a 15-day appeal period are mandatory.  Demolitions must be videographed, and violations could lead to contempt proceedings and personal liability for damages.
title: SC lays down path, timeline that bulldozers must follow

description: Not a political exercise but an intellectual and historical one: Jairam Ramesh
title: Digital archive on all historical material available on Nehru to go live next year

description: Maharashtra Deputy CM Ajit Pawar clarified that his statement about Gautam Adani's involvement in political talks between BJP and NCP five years ago was misconstrued. He emphasized that Adani had no connection to the incident. NCP chief Sharad Pawar supported this, stating that such a significant event wouldn't have remained secret.
title: Remark on Adani presence at NCP-BJP talks misconstrued: Ajit Pawar

description: A parliamentary panel met to discuss the "creamy layer" issue for OBC reservations. The panel raised concerns about the delay in revising the income ceiling for OBC reservations. The current ceiling of Rs 8 lakh was set in 2017 and is due for revision. The panel urged the government to expedite the revision process.
title: Fix creamy layer criteria without delay, say MPs

description: Maharashtra Chief Minister Eknath Shinde and Deputy CM Ajit Pawar underwent security checks at their respective campaign events, mirroring a similar check on former CM Uddhav Thackeray. While Shinde asserted that routine checks shouldn't be a concern, Pawar offered snacks to the inspecting staff.
title: Ajit Pawar offers ‘chakli’ to EC staff as his bag is checked

description: The Indian government has introduced new guidelines to prevent coaching centers from using misleading advertisements. The move comes after investigations revealed numerous instances of exaggerated success claims, including inflated student selection numbers and the use of the same successful candidate's photo across multiple institutes.
title: Centre issues new guidelines to curb misleading ads by coaching institutes

description: As sugarcane cutters in western Maharashtra migrate for the harvest season, their journey coincides with the upcoming elections. With over a million workers potentially unable to vote due to the clashing schedules, concerns about disenfranchisement and potential voter fraud arise.
title: Sugarcane crushing time clashes with poll, 10 lakh may miss vote

description: Naresh Meena, an independent candidate in Rajasthan's Deoli-Uniara constituency, was caught on camera slapping SDM Amit Chaudhary during voting. Meena, a Congress rebel, alleged voting irregularities. The incident sparked outrage, with demands for Meena's arrest from various employee associations. Meena, however, claims he was protesting the SDM's actions and is demanding the reallocation of Samraota village to a nearer sub-division.
title: Independent candidate slaps SDM during Rajasthan bypoll, officials protest

description: Supporters of the Shiv Sena and the Shiv Sena (UBT) clashed violently outside Matoshree Club in Mumbai on Tuesday night.  The clash, which lasted for an hour, was sparked by allegations of money distribution inside the club. Both sides have filed FIRs against each other, accusing the other of assault, molestation, and intimidation.
title: Stones & sticks fly as Sena factions clash in Mumbai

description: Donald Trump has chosen former Democratic Congresswoman Tulsi Gabbard for a surprising role as Director of National Intelligence. Trump praised Gabbard, now identifying as a Republican, for her two decades of service and broad support. Gabbard, who represented Hawaii's 2nd congressional district, left the Democratic Party in 2022, criticizing its stance on war and military intervention.
title: Trump appoints Tulsi Gabbard as director of national intelligence

description: Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi campaigned in Santhal Pargana for the Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) in the Jharkhand assembly elections.  Modi urged voters to support the BJP to protect their land, livelihoods, and daughters. He accused the Congress party of opposing reservation policies and encouraging demographic changes in Jharkhand that threaten tribal communities.
title: Throw out Congress, save ‘roti, beti & maati’: PM Modi in Jharkhand

description: US President-elect Donald Trump has nominated Senator Marco Rubio for the position of United States Secretary of State. Trump praised Rubio as a "fearless warrior" and a staunch advocate for the nation. Born to Cuban immigrants, Rubio's political journey includes serving as a city commissioner, speaker of the Florida House of Representatives, and a three-term US Senator.
title: Trump nominates Senator Marco Rubio for US secretary of state

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi praised Bihar Chief Minister Nitish Kumar's governance during an event in Darbhanga.  Modi inaugurated infrastructure projects worth over ₹12,000 crore, including the foundation stone for an AIIMS. He highlighted the government's focus on healthcare infrastructure, including new AIIMS and medical colleges, and efforts to combat cancer. Modi also addressed flood mitigation strategies for the Kosi-Mithila region.
title: Nitish Kumar has ended ‘jungle raj’ in Bihar, says PM Modi

description: Despite facing immense personal tragedies, children at Hyderabad's Touch Foundation orphanage are overcoming adversity through entrepreneurship. Fourteen-year-old R Poojitha, who started her flower bouquet business 'RMP Flowers', and S Yashaswi, founder of 'RDY Framers Company' specializing in handcrafted photo frames, are just two examples of their resilience.
title: At Hyderabad orphanage, kids turn entrepreneurs

description: During a meeting with Saudi Arabian counterpart Faisal bin Farhan Al Saud, Indian External Affairs Minister S Jaishankar expressed support for a swift ceasefire in Gaza. While condemning terrorism and hostage-taking, Jaishankar stressed the importance of international humanitarian law in responding to the crisis and highlighted India's commitment to a two-state solution for the Palestinian issue.
title: India backs early Gaza truce: EAM Jaishankar to Saudi counterpart

description: An explosion at the Indian Oil refinery in Mathura injured eight workers during the restart of the atmospheric vacuum unit after maintenance. The blast, caused by an overheated furnace line, ignited a fire, leaving three workers critically injured. The injured were promptly hospitalized, with the most severe cases transferred to Delhi. Authorities are investigating the incident.
title: 3 critical after Mathura refinery blast injures 8

description: The Supreme Court instructed the Ajit Pawar-led NCP to refrain from using Sharad Pawar's images in their Maharashtra election campaign. The court urged the faction to establish its own identity and avoid capitalizing on Sharad Pawar's reputation.  The bench also questioned the impact of social media posts on rural voters and highlighted the faction's obligation to adhere to election regulations.
title: Don’t use Sharad Pawar photo, try to stand on own feet: SC to Ajit

description: A vintage Rolls-Royce car, once owned by the Maharani of Baroda, is at the center of a dowry dispute. The car was ordered by Jawaharlal Nehru. The dispute involves the daughter of a Gwalior royal family and a man from a family running an educational institution. The marriage ended shortly after the ceremony.
title: A vintage Rolls-Royce that wrecked a royal marriage

description: The Delhi High Court has overturned the Indian government's decision to revoke the Overseas Citizen of India (OCI) card of a US-based professor accused of "anti-India activities." The court deemed the cancellation notice lacking specific evidence and ordered authorities to issue a new notice with clear grounds for cancellation, ensuring a fair opportunity for the professor to respond.
title: Delhi HC reverses OCI card cancellation for US professor

description: Tensions escalate in Northeast India following the deaths of 10 individuals in Manipur, with tribal groups alleging extrajudicial killings by security forces. Protests erupted in Assam and Mizoram, demanding transparency in the investigation. The incident has further fueled ethnic tensions, with a shutdown enforced in Manipur valley over the alleged abduction of Meitei women and children.
title: Unrest over deaths of 10 ‘militants’ spills over to Assam, Mizoram

description: Following a surge of violence in Manipur, including 13 fatalities since November 7, the Indian Ministry of Home Affairs has deployed 2,500 additional paramilitary personnel to the state. This increases the total central armed police forces deployment to 29,000, bolstering the existing security presence of the Army and Assam Rifles.
title: Manipur on boil again, Centre rushes 2,500 CAPF personnel

description: Counter-Intelligence Kashmir (CIK) apprehended Bhat Navidul Ali, a postgraduate student from Kulgam, for allegedly using social media to promote extremist ideologies and incite anti-government sentiment. CIK claims Ali was influenced by online entities, promoting terrorism in the region and was on the verge of joining militant groups.
title: CIK detains Kashmiri student for ‘glamorizing terrorism’

description: India defeated South Africa by 11 runs in the third T20I to secure a winning 2-1 series lead. Tilak Varma's unbeaten 107 and Abhishek Sharma's quick 50 propelled India to a formidable 219/6. South Africa fought back but fell short, reaching 208/7. Arshdeep Singh's three wickets proved crucial for India's victory.
title: 3rd T20I: Tilak's century takes India to unbeatable series lead

description: Bernard Arnault, chairman of LVMH, is suing Elon Musk's X, alleging the platform used content from Arnault's group of French newspapers without proper compensation. The lawsuit, citing an EU directive, follows a Paris court ruling that ordered X to provide data on its use of the newspapers' content, which X reportedly failed to do.
title: Europe's richest man is suing Elon Musk, this is his 'problem' with him

description: Indian batsman Tilak Varma scored his first T20I century against South Africa in the third T20I. He achieved this feat at 22 years old, becoming the youngest batter to do so against a top-10 team. Varma's unbeaten 107 runs off 56 balls helped India set a challenging target of 219/6.
title: Tilak Varma youngest batter to score T20I century against...

description: President-elect Donald Trump has appointed Elon Musk and Vivek Ramaswamy to lead a new Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE) tasked with drastically reducing the size and scope of the federal government by its 250th anniversary. The move has sparked anxiety among federal employees and raised concerns about potential conflicts of interest given Musk and Ramaswamy's business ties to the government.
title: DOGE days are coming for the US under Trump's two Musketeers

description: Despite a bitter election campaign marked by acrimonious exchanges, President Donald Trump and President-elect Joe Biden met at the White House, signaling a peaceful transfer of power.  Both leaders struck a conciliatory tone, emphasizing a smooth transition. Biden, extending an olive branch, invited Trump for the meeting, a gesture Trump had declined when he lost to Biden in 2020.
title: Joe and Donald warm up by the White House fireplace

description: President-elect Donald Trump is making a triumphant return to Washington, where he will meet with President Joe Biden at the White House and Congressional Republicans to discuss his priorities. Trump's return comes after he contested his 2020 election loss and skipped Biden's inauguration.
title: 'Figure something out': Trump hints he's open to 3rd term in White House in speech to GOP lawmakers

description: San Francisco 49ers quarterback Brock Purdy, despite leading his team to the Super Bowl, remains the lowest-paid starting QB.  However, this could change as the 49ers recognize his worth.  With recent extensions offered to key players like Brandon Aiyuk and a lucrative deal for Deommodore Lenoir, speculation is rife that Purdy might be next in line for a significant payday.
title: 49ers’ contract plans for Brock Purdy unveiled by San Francisco reporter after John Lynch's $92M move

description: Indian cricketer Sanju Samson, after achieving consecutive centuries, has experienced a dip in form with two back-to-back ducks in the ongoing series. This follows his impressive performances, including a blistering century against Bangladesh and a powerful 107 runs off 50 balls in the first match of the current series.
title: After consecutive hundreds, Samson registers successive ducks

description: India celebrates Children's Day annually on November 14th in honor of Pandit Jawaharlal Nehru's birth anniversary.  Schools organize special events to encourage learning and celebrate childhood. This day serves as a reminder to prioritize children's well-being, education, and a safe environment for their growth and development.
title: Happy children's day: Wishes, text, quotes, Fb & WhatsApp status

description: Miller is expected to continue his advocacy for restrictive immigration policies, including limits on H-1B visas. According to a Forbes report, the Trump administration’s stance has often been at odds with economic consensus, which suggests that high-skilled immigrants and international students benefit the U.S. economy. The administration worked to decouple study in the US from work opportunities, particularly through H-1B visa restrictions, making it more challenging for high-skilled foreign nationals to stay and work in the U.S. after graduation.
title: Trump's H-1B hater who will make life hell for Indian techies

description: Microsoft is under fire for its latest attempt to lure users away from Google Chrome. The company's Edge browser now automatically launches on startup, prompting users to import their Chrome data with a pre-selected confirmation button. This tactic, designed to boost Edge's adoption rate, has been met with criticism for its aggressive approach and deceptive design.
title: How this Windows ‘pop-up’ may again lead to Google vs Microsoft tussle

description: In a heartwarming gesture ahead of the third T20I against South Africa, Hardik Pandya presented debutant Ramandeep Singh with his India cap, acknowledging the hard work and dedication that led to this moment.  With the series tied at 1-1, South Africa won the toss and chose to bowl first in Centurion.
title: 'These moments don't come by too often': Hardik to Ramandeep. Watch
Ex-US govt official charged with leaking Israel's plans to strike Iran

description: Former Indian cricketer Aakash Chopra has advised Royal Challengers Bangalore to aggressively pursue Rishabh Pant in the upcoming IPL 2025 auction. He suggested that RCB should be willing to spend up to Rs 25 crore for Pant, highlighting that the small boundaries at M Chinnaswamy Stadium would suit his batting style.
title: 'Even for Rs 25 crore, go for Rishabh Pant'

description: In Yes Minister, bureaucracy isn’t just a system; it’s a labyrinth engineered to perpetuate itself. The civil servants, led by Sir Humphrey Appleby, expertly stonewall any attempt at change, wielding obscure regulations and jargon as weapons. Similarly, DOGE, spearheaded by Elon Musk and Vivek Ramaswamy, is set to streamline government. Yet, like Hacker’s ministry, DOGE faces a government machine skilled in red tape and averse to rapid change. DOGE's task—applying startup efficiency to a complex bureaucracy—is an audacious "Manhattan Project" in its own right.
title: Why Musk-Ramaswamy's DOGE sounds like a Yes Minister spoof
'Your body, my choice': The rise of 'incel culture' under Trump

description: Jio claims its standalone 5G (SA) network architecture, a unique feature in India, delivers faster speeds, lower latency, and improved power efficiency, extending device battery life.
title: Jio prez: Reliance Jio 5G extends battery life by up to 40 percent
Fire breaks out at Sandhya Bazar in south Kolkata, no injuries reported

description: We have learnt that the makers of the ongoing 18th season of Bigg Boss have approached the Kardashian sisters -- Kim, Kylie and Kendall -- to appear on the reality show.
title: Bigg Boss makers approach the Kardashian sisters for Season 18?

description: Supreme Court Justice Gavai, issuing guidelines for property demolitions, emphasized the universal aspiration for a home.  The court ruled that shelter is a fundamental right under Article 21 of the Constitution and condemned 'bulldozer justice'.  Arbitrary demolitions based on accusations violate the rule of law, as the Executive cannot usurp judicial functions by declaring guilt and demolishing properties.
title: 'Ek ghar ka sapna': SC sums up bulldozer action judgment with this shayari

description: Gautam Adani, chairman of Adani Group, announced a $10 billion investment in US energy security and infrastructure projects following Donald Trump's presidential win.  Adani also hosted EU diplomats, showcasing the Adani Group's renewable energy projects in Gujarat, including the upcoming Khavda Renewable Energy Park, planned to be the world's largest.
title: 'Congratulations Trump': Adani to invest $10bn in US energy, infra projects

description: Indian cricketer KL Rahul, in a recent interview, opened up about his evolution as a batsman in limited-overs cricket. He acknowledged initially trying to emulate a power-hitting style but found his true potential by embracing his natural game, inspired by observing Rahul Dravid and Kane Williamson's success with classical techniques.
title: 'Not the nicest thing': KL Rahul on animated chat with LSG owner

description: Cricket legend Shahid Afridi has called for unity amidst confirmation that India will not travel to Pakistan for the 2025 ICC Champions Trophy. The PCB confirmed India's decision, conveyed through the ICC, forcing Pakistan to consider a 'Hybrid Model' for the tournament.
title: 'Keep egos in check': Afridi hopes to see every team in Champions Trophy

description: Blinkit is piloting a program in Delhi NCR to deliver large items like luggage and appliances within 30 minutes. This move challenges traditional e-commerce platforms and aims to increase average order values.  The company is testing a specialized fleet and may expand the program if successful.  Competitor Swiggy Instamart is also exploring similar initiatives but focusing on kitchen appliances.
title: Blinkit's ‘Large order fleet’ service may bring more bad news for Amazon, Flipkart

description: Airbnb CEO Brian Chesky has sparked debate by stating that employee autonomy is largely a myth and that true independence is found in entrepreneurship. As Airbnb prepares for a pivotal year, Chesky advocates for employee integration and collaboration.
title: Airbnb CEO: Start your own company, if you want ….
'Toxic media platform': Why 'The Guardian' quit X after US results

description: The Indian cricket team allowed public viewing of their training sessions in Perth. This decision followed an Australian media report claiming the training sessions were closed. The team management confirmed that no official request was made to restrict public access. The team will use the sessions for match simulation and a warm-up game against India A.
title: 'No request' from BCCI but Oz media report claims India wanted...

description: Scammers are using fake digital wedding invitations sent via WhatsApp to spread malware and steal personal information. These malicious files, disguised as wedding invitations, can infect phones and grant hackers access to messages, contacts, and even financial data.
title: How wedding invites on WhatsApp are taking control of phones; stealing money & more

description: The Indian stock market experienced a significant drop for the second consecutive day, with the Sensex plummeting over 984 points, marking its lowest point in four months. This decline, fueled by soaring retail inflation and foreign fund withdrawals, wiped out Rs 13 lakh crore from investor wealth in just two sessions.
title: Bloodbath on D-street: Investors lose Rs 13 lakh cr in 2 days; why market is falling
Iranian man, once pardoned, hanged after victim's family revokes forgiveness
'No law and order': Political blamegame erupts after doc stabbed in Chennai
'Stand up on your legs': SC snubs Ajit Pawar's NCP over use of uncle's photos

description: Stoa School, a Bengaluru-based edtech startup backed by Zerodha founder Nithin Kamath, has shut down after four years. The company, which offered a six-month MBA program, announced its closure in a message on Tuesday, expressing gratitude to its team, investors, and users.
title: Nithin Kamath-backed 4-year-old edtech startup shuts down, read co-founders message

description: The Himachal Pradesh High Court has declared the appointment of six chief parliamentary secretaries as unconstitutional.  Twelve BJP MLAs challenged the appointments, arguing that the state government overstepped its authority by creating offices not recognized by the Constitution. The court agreed, voiding the appointments and ordering the immediate withdrawal of any benefits or facilities they received.
title: Big blow to CM Sukhu: Himachal HC voids 6 top appointments
'Bag-checked': Shinde, Ajit Pawar post frisking videos as Uddhav questions EC

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi is embarking on a three-nation tour to Nigeria, Brazil, and Guyana from November 16th to 21st. The visit aims to bolster bilateral ties, with Modi attending the G20 Summit in Brazil and engaging in high-level talks in Nigeria and Guyana.
title: PM Modi to attend G20 Summit in Brazil, visit Nigeria and Guyana from November 16-20

description: Russia's parliament has passed a law banning the 'promotion of childlessness' as part of a larger effort to boost the country's declining birth rate. The law targets media content that encourages people not to have children and includes fines for violations.  This move aligns with Russia's ongoing rejection of what it considers 'Western liberal values,' which has also resulted in restrictions on LGBTQ+ rights and adoptions.
title: 'Western policy destructive': Russia bans 'propaganda' of childless lifestyle

description: A bus carrying a marriage party from Prayagraj to Noida collided with a truck on the Prayagraj-Kanpur highway near Mohar village, resulting in the death of three passengers, including a child.  The accident, which occurred early Wednesday, left nine others injured. The injured were taken to nearby hospitals, with three critically injured individuals transferred to Hallet hospital in Kanpur.
title: 3 dead, 9 injured after bus carrying baratis rams into truck

description: Virat Kohli has begun his preparations for the Border-Gavaskar Trophy in Perth, hitting the nets with focus on countering short-pitched deliveries. Arriving early in Australia, Kohli aims to acclimatize to the conditions and refine his technique against pace bowling, drawing from his past experiences at the WACA and Optus Stadium.
title: Virat Kohli in focus: Intense net session begins for BGT

description: Arjun Tendulkar, son of cricket legend Sachin, achieved his first five-wicket haul in first-class cricket. Playing for Goa against Arunachal Pradesh, he took 5 wickets for 25 runs, leading Goa to a dominant position. This milestone signifies Arjun's growing prowess in domestic cricket as he continues to build his career.
title: Arjun Tendulkar claims maiden five-wicket haul in Ranji Trophy

description: A Chennai oncologist, Dr. Balaji Jaganathan, was critically injured after being stabbed multiple times by a former patient's son. The assailant, Vignesh, attacked the doctor at Kalaignar Multi-Speciality Hospital due to grievances related to his mother's cancer treatment. Vignesh was apprehended while trying to escape, and doctors at the hospital staged a flash strike to protest the lack of security.
title: Chennai doctor stabbed by disgruntled patient's son at hospital

description: The Supreme Court issued guidelines for property demolitions, emphasising due process.  Demolition solely due to an occupant's accused or convicted status is deemed unconstitutional.  Mandatory show cause notices, video recording of demolitions, and compensation for unlawful actions are mandated. These guidelines, applicable nationwide, aim to protect the right to shelter and prevent arbitrary demolitions.
title: 15-day notice, videography of demolition: SC issues guidelines on ‘bulldozer justice’

description: A newlywed woman from Rajasthan's Dausa district postponed her post-wedding rituals to cast her vote in the assembly bypoll, emphasizing the importance of civic duty. The Dausa by-election is particularly significant due to high-profile candidates. Seven constituencies in Rajasthan are holding bypolls, with results expected on November 23rd.
title: Watch: A day after wedding, bride casts vote for assembly bypoll in Rajasthan's Dausa

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi inaugurated the foundation stone for a new AIIMS in Darbhanga, Bihar, aiming to enhance healthcare accessibility in the region and beyond. He emphasized the government's comprehensive approach to healthcare, including disease prevention, affordable treatment, and infrastructure development.
title: PM Modi lays foundation stone for AIIMS in Bihar's Darbhanga

description: Dense fog enveloped Delhi, reducing visibility to zero in several areas, including the Ghazipur Landfill and the Delhi airport. The fog caused travel disruptions and health issues for residents, with the Air Quality Index reaching 'very poor' levels.
title: Ghazipur landfill vanishes! Smog deepens in Delhi, lowering visibility

description: Pakistan captain Mohammad Rizwan has stated that Indian cricketers would be welcomed in Pakistan for the 2025 Champions Trophy. However, uncertainty surrounds India's participation in the tournament if it's held in Pakistan. The PCB is seeking clarification from the ICC regarding India's stance, as they consider withdrawing if hosting rights are revoked.
title: 'Rahul, SKY ke liye ... ': Pak skipper Rizwan on 2025 CT stand-off

description: Vicky Kaushal will be seen as Lord Parashurama in the upcoming film 'Mahavatar'. The film will be directed by Amar Kaushik. Dinesh Vijan is producing the film under his banner Maddock Films. 'Mahavatar' is scheduled to release in theatres on Christmas 2026. The film will start production in November 2025. Vicky Kaushal is currently busy with his other projects.
title: Vicky Kaushal drops powerful first look as Lord Parashurama for ‘Mahavatar’

description: KL Rahul has spoken out about his animated cha with Lucknow Super Giants' owner Sanjiv Goenka after a disappointing loss to Sunrisers Hyderabad in the last IPL season. The incident, which was on camera during live broadcast, occurred after LSG failed to qualify for the playoffs. Rahul has since parted ways with the team and will enter the upcoming IPL auction.
title: 'Not the nicest thing': KL Rahul on animated chat with LSG owner

description: This NYU study opens up a new dimension in memory science, suggesting that our entire body could play a role in storing memories. As we continue to explore the potential of these findings, we may discover even more ways in which our organs and cells contribute to memory and learning.
title: Can skin and liver 'remember'? Does our body store memories everywhere?

description: Bhojpuri actress Akshara Singh received a threatening call demanding Rs 50 lakh ransom. The caller warned of dire consequences if the money wasn't paid within two days.  Akshara's legal advisor reported the incident to the Danapur police.  Police detained a suspect from Bhojpur, but preliminary investigations suggest it wasn't a ransom call but a dispute related to an event invitation.
title: Bhojpuri actor Akshara Singh receives death threat

description: Bollywood stars, including Salman Khan and Shah Rukh Khan, are facing a surge in death threats and extortion attempts, raising concerns about the resurgence of underworld influence in the film industry. While gang-related violence and extortion are not new to Bollywood, recent incidents involving high-profile figures have prompted increased security measures.
title: Salman death threat to Shah Rukh extortion demand: Is Bollywood a soft target?

description: Volcanic eruptions from Mount Lewotobi Laki-laki in Indonesia forced international airlines to suspend services to and from Bali due to safety concerns over volcanic ash clouds. Thousands of travelers were stranded as flights were canceled, leaving many frustrated and seeking alternative routes home.
title: Bali volcano eruption: Tourists stranded after ash clouds force flight cancellations

description: Naresh Meena, an independent candidate from Deoli-Uniara, was filmed assaulting SDM Amit Choudhary at Samravata polling station in Rajasthan. Meena, a former Congress leader, was suspended after contesting independently in the by-election.
title: Watch: Rajasthan bypoll candidate slaps SDM amid voting dispute

description: Swiggy, the Indian food delivery giant, debuted on the stock market with its shares opening at a premium. CEO of competitor Zomato, Deepinder Goyal, congratulated Swiggy on social media, sparking positive responses from users. The IPO was well-received, exceeding expectations and highlighting the growth of India's tech and food delivery sectors.
title: Zomato CEO's heartfelt message as rival Swiggy makes market debut

description: India captain Rohit Sharma is  training in Mumbai, aiming to be match-ready for the Border-Gavaskar Trophy in Australia. However, his participation in the first Test remains uncertain as he awaits the birth of his second child. In his absence, Jasprit Bumrah will lead the team, with the one vacant opening slot being contested by Abhimanyu Easwaran and KL Rahul.
title: Rohit continues to train in Mumbai, no clarity on Australia departure

description: Addressing a rally in Maharashtra, Home Minister Amit Shah launched a scathing attack on the Congress party, criticizing their stance on Article 370, Muslim reservation, and the Ram Temple. Shah asserted that Article 370 would not be reinstated, even if "Indira Gandhi were to return from heaven.
title: 'Even if Indira Gandhi returns from heaven ... ': What Amit Shah said on Article 370

description: India's higher education institutions rely heavily on academic scores and publication records when hiring faculty. This approach often overlooks candidates with valuable industry experience and practical skills. To align with global best practices, the recruitment process should adopt a more holistic approach, considering a broader range of qualifications and expertise.
title: Recruiting profs in India: What UGC needs to change and why

description: British rock band Coldplay is bringing their Music of the Spheres World Tour to Ahmedabad's Narendra Modi Stadium on January 25, 2025. Tickets, priced from Rs 2,500 to Rs 12,500, will be available exclusively through BookMyShow starting November 16, 2024, at 6 PM.
title: Coldplay Ahmedabad concert announced: How to book tickets, pricing & more

description: Celebrated couple Virat Kohli and Anushka Sharma were spotted enjoying family time with daughter Vamika in Perth.  Kohli, in Australia for the Border-Gavaskar Trophy, began his preparations for the Test series against Australia. His recent form has been a concern, with lower-than-usual run averages, adding pressure to his performance in the upcoming series.
title: Virat and Anushka spend quality time with Vamika in Perth

description: Zomato congratulates Swiggy on its successful IPO listing with a heartwarming Instagram post, drawing parallels to its own journey in 2021.
title: How Netflix, Amazon & others reacted to Zomato's 'Jai and Veeru' message to Swiggy

description: Former Pakistani wicketkeeper Rashid Latif has voiced his strong stance against Pakistan playing cricket with India in any tournament. He believes that the ICC should withhold hosting rights from both nations until their bilateral issues are resolved.
title: 'Had I been in power...': Latif furious over India's stand for CT
Watch: PM Modi's gesture as Nitish Kumar bows down to touch his feet

description: In a landmark judgment, the Supreme Court has issued strict guidelines to halt the unlawful demolition of homes belonging to accused individuals. The court emphasized that 'bulldozer justice' violates fundamental rights and undermines the rule of law. The guidelines mandate due process, prohibit collective punishment, and ensure accountability for arbitrary actions by authorities.
title: 'Collective punishment': Why Supreme Court declared 'bulldozer justice' illegal

description: Pakistani TikToker Imsha Rehman's private videos were leaked online, sparking outrage and raising concerns about privacy. The incident follows a similar controversy involving TikTok star Minahil Malik, whose private video surfaced in October, drawing criticism and support.
title: Now Pak TikToker Imsha Rehman’s alleged obscene video leaked online

description: NASA astronaut Sunita Williams addressed concerns about her health after images showed her looking thinner during her extended stay on the International Space Station. She clarified that the change in appearance is due to fluid shifts caused by microgravity and not a health issue. NASA confirmed her good health, highlighting her rigorous exercise routine and regular health evaluations.
title: Stranded Sunita Williams dismisses severe weight loss rumours

description: Elon Musk and Vivek Ramaswamy, recently appointed by Donald Trump to lead the Department of Government Efficiency ("DOGE"), sparked a meme fest on social media.  Both shared Doge meme-inspired images on X, referencing the department's acronym and the popular Shiba Inu meme.
title: Musk, Ramaswamy go full 'Doge' with new Trump role as meme fest takes over X

description: A Sydney woman's harborside proposal to her partner went viral, sparking debate about gender roles. While some criticized the woman for defying tradition, others praised her initiative and celebrated the couple's love, highlighting evolving societal views on relationships.
title: 'Girl! Get up & stop embarrassing us': Woman’s proposal leaves internet divided

description: The Supreme Court criticized the Defence Colony Welfare Association (DCWA) for illegally occupying the historic Shaikh Ali 'Gumti' tomb. The court questioned the DCWA's justification for the occupation and criticized the Archaeological Survey of India (ASI) for allowing it.
title: 'How dare you enter tomb': SC slams Delhi RWA for office at Lodi-era monument
'Threat to democracy?': Musk reacts after Trump picks him to lead 'DOGE'

description: Dense fog enveloped Delhi on Wednesday morning, leading to the rerouting of several flights at Indira Gandhi International Airport.  The fog, which the IMD reported began around 5.30am., significantly reduced visibility.  Adding to the city's woes, air quality remained in the 'very poor' category for the 15th consecutive day.
title: Several flights diverted due to low visibility conditions at Delhi airport

description: Swiggy, the food and grocery delivery company, experienced a successful stock market debut on Wednesday.  Shares opened at a 7.69% increase on the NSE, reaching Rs 420. The company's IPO, totaling Rs 11,327 crore, was fully subscribed, indicating strong investor confidence.
title: Swiggy's stock surges on debut, lists 7.7% above issue price at Rs 420 on NSE

description: Veteran cricketers Ravichandran Ashwin and Steve Smith are expected to play pivotal roles in the upcoming Border-Gavaskar Trophy. Ashwin, renowned for his spin bowling prowess, has consistently challenged Smith's batting technique.  Ashwin shared insights into his strategic approach against Smith, highlighting their intriguing battles and his understanding of Smith's strengths and weaknesses.
title: Watch: Ashwin gives an insight on his mind games with Smith

description: Swiggy's shares soared 7.7% on their debut, listing at Rs 420 after a hugely successful IPO that saw the company valued at $1.4 billion. This landmark event is set to create approximately 500 new crorepatis among Swiggy's employees, thanks to a generous Rs 9,000 crore ESOP payout.
title: Swiggy IPO: 9 execs who will become richer by Rs 50 crore or more

description: Election officials in Maharashtra are conducting security checks on the luggage of all political leaders during their election rallies. This follows controversy over the frisking of Uddhav Thackeray's bags, which he felt was politically motivated. Officials maintain they are simply following Election Commission guidelines, pointing to similar checks on other prominent figures like Nitin Gadkari and Raj Thackeray.
title: Frisking row: Luggage of Nitin Gadkari, Vinod Tawde were also checked, say officials

description: Former Indian cricketer Suresh Raina emphasizes the importance of strong character and a fighting spirit for success in Australia as India gears up for the Border-Gavaskar Trophy. Raina highlights Virat Kohli's crucial role, drawing parallels to his exceptional performance in the 2014-15 tour, while acknowledging his recent struggles.
title: Exclusive | Jurel can be India's X-factor in Australia, says Raina

description: President-elect Donald Trump is assembling his administration for his second term, prioritizing loyalty from his 2024 campaign. Notable appointments include Elon Musk and Vivek Ramaswamy to streamline government, John Ratcliffe's return as CIA director, and prominent roles for Mike Huckabee, Pete Hegseth, and others reflecting Trump's policy agenda.
title: Trump cabinet 2.0: Full list of key appointments including Musk, Ramaswamy, Ratcliffe

description: Dinesh Karthik believes Sanju Samson has cemented his place as India's T20I opener alongside Yashasvi Jaiswal. Samson's recent form, including back-to-back centuries, has impressed experts like Zaheer Khan, who praised his shot selection and maturity. Karthik highlighted Samson's technical adjustments and composure as key factors in his success.
title: 'Sanju Samson has cemented his spot as T20I opener'

description: World leaders gathered at the COP29 climate summit in Baku, with UK Prime Minister Keir Starmer taking center stage. Starmer announced ambitious new climate goals for the UK, aiming to reduce greenhouse gas emissions by at least 81% by 2035.
title: UK PM unveils ambitious new climate goals even as top world leaders give COP29 a miss

description: Former Australian all-rounder Shane Lee has criticized his ex-teammate Ricky Ponting for his comments on Virat Kohli's form, suggesting it might backfire by motivating the Indian star ahead of the Border-Gavaskar Trophy. Lee anticipates a heated series, fueled by Ponting's remarks. The first Test begins on November 22 in Perth.
title: Fired-up Kohli is Australia's worry after Ponting's 'bad move'

description: The Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) faces significant financial losses if the 2025 Champions Trophy is moved or postponed due to India's refusal to participate. The PCB risks losing USD 65 million in hosting fees and potential ICC sanctions. The standoff arises from India's security concerns, despite other nations touring Pakistan recently.
title: How much money Pakistan can lose if CT is moved or postponed

description: Taking a break from campaigning, Rahul Gandhi explored Wayanad's scenic beauty, including its longest zipline, to promote tourism after recent landslides impacted the region.  He engaged with locals, acknowledging their struggles and praising their resilience. Both Rahul and Priyanka Gandhi emphasized Wayanad's untapped tourism potential, urging visitors to support the region's recovery.
title: Watch: Rahul Gandhi tries Kerala's longest zipline in bid to promote tourism

description: The Supreme Court established strict guidelines to prevent authorities from demolishing properties without due process. The court emphasized that officials who illegally demolish homes will face consequences, and affected families will be compensated.  The court stressed that India's secular nature demands equal application of the law, regardless of religion.
title: Bulldozer justice: Executive can't become judge, demolish house of accused, SC says

description: Taiwan's ministry of national defence detected 24 Chinese aircraft and 6 naval vessels near its territory, with 15 of the aircraft crossing the median line of the Taiwan Strait. This follows a similar incident the previous day.  Taiwan's President convened a security meeting, reaffirming their commitment to national security amidst heightened tensions stemming from China's increased military activities.
title: Chinese military activity near Taiwan intensifies, 24 PLA aircraft detected

description: A goods train carrying iron ore derailed in Telangana's Peddapalli district, causing significant disruptions to passenger train services.  The incident, involving eleven wagons, led to the cancellation of 20 passenger trains, while others faced partial cancellations, diversions, rescheduling, or regulations.  Restoration efforts are currently underway to normalize train movement.
title: 11 wagons of goods train derail in Telangana

description: Former Pakistani cricketer Basit Ali has suggested separating India and Pakistan into different groups for the 2025 Champions Trophy if the International Cricket Council (ICC) proceeds with a hybrid model. Ali believes this would alleviate logistical and political issues but acknowledges it's unlikely as India-Pakistan matches are major revenue generators.
title: 'Duniya bewakoof hai': Basit Ali gives Ind-Pak stand-off solution

description: Former Australian pacer Brett Lee believes India's overconfidence led to their unexpected Test series defeat against New Zealand. Lee highlighted India's impatient batting and lack of preparation as key factors in their losses. Despite this setback, Lee expects India to bounce back stronger in the upcoming Border-Gavaskar Trophy against Australia.
title: New Zealand caught 'overconfident' India off guard: Brett Lee

description: Mohammed Shami is poised to make his return to competitive cricket after a year-long absence due to an ankle injury. The Indian pacer will represent Bengal in their upcoming Ranji Trophy match against Madhya Pradesh, aiming to prove his fitness and potentially earn a late call-up to India's Test squad for the Border-Gavaskar Trophy in Australia.
title: Can Shami make a late entry into India's squad in Australia?

description: A Jaipur man had a close call after he drove his Mahindra Thar onto railway tracks, purportedly to film a social media video. The incident, captured on video, shows the man attempting to drive the SUV off the tracks as a goods train approaches.
title: Watch: Stunt with Thar on railway tracks goes wrong after vehicle gets stuck

description: A devastating collision between a speeding multi-utility vehicle and a container truck in Dehradun has claimed the lives of six young individuals and left one critically injured. The victims, all in their late teens and early twenties, were traveling near ONGC Chowk when the tragic accident occurred.
title: Dehradun bizman flagged highspeed MUV before fatal crash that killed 6

description: Bollywood actor and BJP leader Mithun Chakraborty refused to apologize for a speech he gave in Dhanbad, despite receiving a threat from a Pakistani individual demanding he do so. Chakraborty denied making any hateful remarks and stated he would only apologize if he had done something wrong. During a campaign event, his wallet was briefly misplaced but quickly recovered.
title: Mithun Chakraborty's 'lost' wallet sends BJP workers into a tizzy at Jharkhand rally

description: President-elect Donald Trump has appointed Elon Musk and Vivek Ramaswamy to lead the newly formed Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE). Tasked with transforming federal governance into a streamlined model, the duo will leverage their private-sector experience to seek out inefficiencies in the $6.5 trillion annual federal spending by July 4, 2026.
title: 'Manhattan Project': Trump taps Musk, Ramaswamy to 'DOGE', 'shock' US govt

description: A recent episode of Bigg Boss 18 witnessed a dramatic physical altercation between contestants Avinash Mishra and Digvijay Rathee, leaving fellow housemate Shilpa Shirodkar shaken after being inadvertently pushed. This incident has raised concerns about escalating tensions within the house.
title: Bigg Boss 18: Physical fight between Avinash Mishra & Digvijay Rathee
Trump appoints television host, army veteran Pete Hegseth as his defense secretary
UK writer Samantha Harvey wins 2024 Booker Prize

description: Indian cricketer KL Rahul faced a tough choice when asked to pick his ideal IPL 2025 teammate from among Rohit Sharma, Virat Kohli, and MS Dhoni. Rahul, released by the Lucknow Super Giants, will be a sought-after player in the upcoming IPL mega auction. While he doesn't actively seek captaincy, he's open to leading if given the opportunity.
title: Rohit, Virat or MSD as IPL 2025 teammate? Rahul in a pickle - Watch

description: Ahead of the Border Gavaskar Trophy, a war of words has erupted between India's coach Gautam Gambhir and former Australian captain Ricky Ponting over Virat Kohli's form, with Gambhir defending his players and Ponting clarifying his intentions. The five-Test series begins on November 22 at the Optus Stadium in Perth.
title: Ponting hits back at Gambhir, calls him 'prickly character'

description: Delhi's air quality has been classified as 'very poor' for 15 consecutive days, with the primary pollutant being PM10.  This harmful particulate matter originates from sources like vehicle emissions and industrial activities, posing significant health risks to residents.
title: Smog blankets Delhi as AQI stays in 'very poor' range for 15th consecutive day

description: Voting is underway in Kerala's Wayanad Lok Sabha constituency for the by-election. Congress leader Priyanka Gandhi Vadra is making her electoral debut against 15 other candidates. The bypoll was necessitated after Rahul Gandhi vacated the seat. Wayanad, a Congress stronghold, will see its 14.7 lakh voters decide the outcome.
title: Wayanad bypolls: Voting under way for Priyanka Gandhi Vadra's electoral debut

description: Kartik Aaryan's Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 has shown impressive resilience at the box office, collecting Rs 5 crore nett on its second Monday. While this marks a 45 percent drop from its Friday collections, the hold is better than expected for a post-holiday period. According to Sacnilk, the film is estimated to add another Rs 4.25 crore on Tuesday, maintaining a lead over Singham Again, which has begun to slow in its second week.
title: Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3 day 12 collection: Kartik Aaryan's film earns Rs 4.25 crore

description: West Indies have made two changes to their T20I squad for the remaining matches against England. Andre Russell is out due to an ankle injury and is replaced by Shamar Springer. Alzarri Joseph returns from suspension, replacing Shamar Joseph. The hosts will be looking to bounce back from a 0-2 deficit in the five-match series.
title: Russell ruled out as WI make key changes for remaining England T20Is

description: US President-elect Donald Trump has appointed William "Bill" McGinley as his White House counsel. McGinley, who previously served as Trump's White House cabinet secretary, brings extensive legal experience to the role. Donald Trump praised McGinley's legal acumen and highlighted his commitment to advancing the "America First" agenda and election integrity.
title: William McGinley to serve as White House counsel in Trump’s new term

description: President-elect Donald Trump has appointed Steven C Witkoff, a prominent real estate investor and philanthropist, as Special Envoy to the Middle East. Witkoff, with a successful track record in property development and a history of leadership in various organizations, has been tasked with promoting stability and peace in the region.
title: Trump selects real estate tycoon Steven Witkoff as Middle East envoy

description: Two elderly residents of a displacement camp in Manipur's Jiribam were found dead, one with bullet wounds and the other charred, following a counteroffensive by security forces against alleged militants.  Tribal groups dispute the official account, claiming the deceased were village volunteers and demanding an apology from the CRPF.  The incident has sparked protests and heightened tensions in the region.
title: Bodies of two relief camp inmates found at site of Manipur gunfight

description: US President-elect Donald Trump has appointed Tesla CEO Elon Musk and Vivek Ramaswamy to lead the department of government efficiency (DOGE).  Their mission is to reduce bureaucracy, cut wasteful spending, and reorganise federal agencies. This initiative aims to create a smaller, more efficient government by the 250th anniversary of American Independence.
title: Trump says Elon Musk, Vivek Ramaswamy to lead department of government efficiency

description: Ajit Pawar disclosed his involvement in political discussions with the BJP five years prior, stating that prominent figures like Amit Shah, Gautam Adani, and Sharad Pawar were present. He emphasized that decisions were made collectively, and while he faced the repercussions, the reasons behind Sharad Pawar's eventual reluctance remain unknown.
title: Adani, Sharad Pawar, Shah and Praful were at BJP-NCP talks 5 years ago: Ajit

description: Three men from Kodungaiyur were apprehended at Chennai airport for smuggling high-grade cannabis worth ₹50 lakh. The trio, identified as Mohammad Yusuff, Haroon, and Farook, had concealed the drug inside snack packets to evade airport security. They had flown from Bangkok to Delhi and then to Chennai in an attempt to avoid suspicion.
title: Ganja goes incognito: Chennai trio’s snack packet smuggling scheme foiled

description: India's retail inflation surged to a 14-month high in October, driven by soaring food prices, exceeding the central bank's target and diminishing hopes of an interest rate cut.  However, industrial output rebounded in September, fueled by growth in the manufacturing sector.
title: Retail inflation surges to a 14-month high of 6.2% in October

description: Nisha Madhulika, a former teacher, has become a YouTube sensation and one of India's wealthiest female YouTubers at 65. Her journey began to combat loneliness, leading her to share simple Indian recipes in Hindi. With over 14.5 million subscribers, she has amassed a net worth of Rs 43 crore.
title: Meet one of the India's richest female YouTuber, who started her channel at 52

description: Police in Noida arrested a 46-year-old man for allegedly running a cannabis farm out of his apartment. Rahul Chaudhury was found with 80 plants worth an estimated Rs 60 lakh, along with growing equipment. Chaudhury, who reportedly learned to cultivate cannabis online, allegedly sold the drugs on the dark web.
title: Weed garden in Gr Noida flat unearthed: Bought seeds online; used AC, lights 24x7

description: Tragedy struck a family in Hyderabad's Old City when a 25-year-old man allegedly murdered his wife in a fit of jealous rage. Fayaz Qureshi is accused of stabbing his wife, Khamar Begum, multiple times before setting her ablaze. The couple, who had two young children, reportedly had a history of domestic disputes fueled by Qureshi's suspicions of infidelity.
title: Hyderabad labourer stabs wife, sets her on fire on suspicion of having affair

description: Two villagers were injured in a shooting incident in Sheopur district, Madhya Pradesh, on Monday night, sparking accusations between the Congress and BJP. The incident occurred in Dhanaycha and Dangpura villages after campaigning ended for the Vijaypur assembly bypoll. Eight armed men allegedly threatened villagers and opened fire when they refused to surrender their voter slips.
title: Two injured in violence ahead of MP bypoll

description: Captain Savita Singh, potentially India's sole female helicopter pilot in election campaigns, is challenging norms and surprising crowds in rural areas.  Her presence as a woman pilot often elicits shock and even skepticism from some passengers.  Beyond the novelty, she navigates demanding conditions, from navigating crowds to facing security concerns and limited facilities, highlighting the stark realities of campaign flying.
title: Meet the bahin flying politicians to their Ladki scheme speeches

description: Former South African cricketer Paul Adams has sparked debate by claiming Nathan Lyon is a more "complete" bowler than Ravichandran Ashwin. Adams credits Lyon's adaptability to diverse conditions, particularly his overspin, as giving him an edge. He also believes India will miss Mohammed Shami's pace in the upcoming series against Australia.
title: 'Nathan Lyon more complete bowler than Ravichandran Ashwin'

description: Nawab Malik, NCP candidate from Mankhurd Shivaji Nagar, stated that his party will not be part of a government that promotes divisive politics. He condemned the 'Batenge toh Katenge' slogan and criticized the BJP's proposed anti-conversion law, calling it misleading.
title: We won’t join govt if BJP raises disputed issues, says NCP’s Malik

description: Ayodhya was placed under high alert following a terror threat issued by SFJ chief Gurpatwant Singh Pannun. Pannun threatened to target the Ram Temple and other Hindu temples. Security forces were deployed in large numbers. Surveillance was increased with CCTV and drone cameras. The city was transformed into a fortress to ensure the safety of residents and pilgrims.
title: Security upped in Ayodhya after threat by pro-Khalistan SFJ chief Pannun

description: A video showing BJP leader Raosaheb Danve kicking an aide during a photo session with Shiv Sena's Arjun Khotkar went viral.  The incident occurred after a meeting between the two former rivals in Jalna. Danve's aide downplayed the incident as jocular. Opposition parties criticized Danve's behavior, while BJP members defended him.
title: BJP's Raosaheb Danve’s kick video kicks up a furore; aide calls it a joke

description: Election officials conducted a luggage check on Uddhav Thackeray at Latur airport. This is the second time his bags were checked during the election campaign. Officials stated that they were following Election Commission guidelines and that similar checks were conducted on other politicians. Thackeray questioned if the same rules were applied to PM Modi.
title: ‘Why am I the first customer?’: Poll officials check Uddhav Thackrey’s bags 2nd time
